														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1280125">
									

<p>Gah! The Foundation is not remotely at the forefront of medical research. Dealing with dangerous stuff doesn't really mean much of anything in that regard. The Foundation cannot have a very large or well-connected medical research division, due to secrecy and scale reasons. They are smaller than, say, Hopkins or NIH, have less medical resources than Hopkins or NIH, and probably have worse scientists than any major research institution out there. The Foundation is very good at some things, but not every last little thing. And there's no way that it makes sense for them to be anything but crap at medical research.</p>

