				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/anaxagoras" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1019930); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1019930&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610164759" alt="Anaxagoras" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1019930)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/anaxagoras" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1019930); return false;" >Anaxagoras</a></span> <span class="odate time_1318487061 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">13 Oct 2011 06:24</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1280198">
									

<p>I'm sorry, I prefer my top-secret world-spanning organizations to actually face realistic consequences for being so.</p>
<p>Look, the Foundation literally cannot be larger than a million people, okay? Even with all the amnesiacs in the world, that won't be enough to stop a catastrophic secrecy breach in only a few years. A tiny, tiny fraction of that is medical research. Because, get this, the Foundation has no actual reason to do medical research. SCPs are either so different from normal stuff that any research conclusions drawn have no relevance anywhere else, or respond to standard stuff in which case the Foundation won't need to do much of anything.</p>
<p>The ruthlessness argument is valid to a point, but that won't get it far enough. Plus, the Foundation focuses pretty heavily on SCPs. They aren't every industry ever, and they certainly aren't better at every industry ever than every industry ever.</p>
<p>Anyhow, this is getting me far angrier than I ought to let it. Of course I have strong opinions. What's the point of having opinions otherwise? Night all.</p>

							</div>

								
					
